From: MIRA orchestrator (B10 lens — Hub functional readiness)
Date: 2026-06-19
Subject: chore(hub): remove 2 stale @ts-expect-error directives so `tsc --noEmit` is clean

Full-project `npx tsc --noEmit` in mira-hub (origin/main@29d9e920, project tsconfig,
shipped node_modules) reports exactly 2 errors, both TS2578 "Unused '@ts-expect-error'
directive" in TEST files — the suppressed lines no longer type-error, so the directives
are redundant. Zero production-code errors; zero stranger-reachable impact. This patch
removes the two dead directives so a full typecheck is green.

CAVEAT before merge: confirm the repo's CI typecheck step uses the same tsconfig as a
bare `tsc --noEmit` (if CI runs `next build`, test files may be excluded and these never
fire there). The fix is correct for the project's own root tsconfig either way.

Verify:
  cd mira-hub && git apply --check ../wiki/orchestrator/patches/2026-06-19-B10-tsc-stale-ts-expect-error.patch
  # then, from repo root, against origin/main:
  git apply -p1 --check wiki/orchestrator/patches/2026-06-19-B10-tsc-stale-ts-expect-error.patch
  # apply + re-typecheck:
  git apply -p1 wiki/orchestrator/patches/2026-06-19-B10-tsc-stale-ts-expect-error.patch
  cd mira-hub && npx tsc --noEmit   # expect: clean

